text: Cameron Lewis Moir-Pring (born 22 January 1998) is an English professional footballer who plays as a left back for Portsmouth, on loan from Bristol City. ==Career== Born in Cheltenham, Pring began his career with his hometown club Cheltenham Town, joining their youth academy as a 14-year-old in 2012. In January 2016 he moved to Bristol City. In January 2017, Pring moved to Guernsey on a youth loan, making 4 appearances in the Isthmian League Division One South. He then spent further loan spells at Merthyr Town, Aldershot Town and Hereford during the 2017–18 season. He moved on loan to Newport County in August 2018. He made his debut for Newport on 11 September 2018 against Swindon Town in a 1–0 EFL Trophy defeat, and on 17 November 2018 he scored his first senior goal in a 2–0 win against Colchester United. He returned to hometown club Cheltenham Town on loan in January 2019 until the end of the 2018–19 season. On 3 July 2019, Pring signed for League Two side Walsall on a season-long loan deal. On 1 September 2020 he moved on loan to Portsmouth for the 2020–21 season. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:English footballers Category:Cheltenham Town F.C. players Category:Bristol City F.C. players Category:Guernsey F.C. players Category:Merthyr Town F.C. players Category:Aldershot Town F.C. players Category:Hereford F.C. players Category:Newport County A.F.C. players Category:Walsall F.C. players Category:Portsmouth F.C. players Category:Association football fullbacks Category:English Football League players
